description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a Staff Nurse (E Grade) to join our Outpatients nursing team located in Central London, W1G 6HL (close to Regents Park &amp; Baker Street tube stations).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Established in 1932, The London Clinic is one of the UK’s largest private hospitals, with state-of-the-art facilities located on Harley Street. Our Consulting Rooms and Outpatients Centre provides a medical environment in which a wide range of out-patient procedures are undertaken such as: Minor Gynae procedures, sterile dressings, Removal of stitches and clips, Wound swabs, Joint Injections, Rigid sigmoidoscopies and Photodynamic therapy to pre-cancerous skin lesions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Job Description&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Staff Nurse, you will work with senior and junior staff co-ordinating and delivering quality standards of nursing care following a patient centred model of practice in keeping with the Clinic’s Philosophy, The Departments Policies/Protocols and NMC guidelines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Job Type: This is a full-time, permanent position, working 37.5 hours per week; Monday to Friday.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shifts: Earlies &amp; lates to cover the Outpatients service from 8am to 8pm. The early morning shift could start at 7.30am and the late could be until 8.30pm.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Benefits package: We offer a comprehensive package which includes a contribution pension scheme (total annual contribution up to 20%), Private Medical Healthcare,187.5 hours plus Bank Holidays (annual leave), season ticket travel loan, and a wide range of discounts with a variety of retailers and services. We also offer excellent career development; with clear career pathways and access to further education.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary: The attractive salary range for this role is £33,877 - £37,950 (Inclusive), and will be dependent upon skills and experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Duties &amp; Responsibilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for individualised patient care of the highest standard working closely with the Consultants, nursing colleagues and clerical staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the provision of excellent evidence based care for patients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a chaperone where necessary and co-ordinate and assist Minor Gynae / Colposcopy / Hysteroscopy Clinics independently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote research based practice and clinical audit and evaluate change in practice and service delivery as a result of this to ensure quality outcomes for all patients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide clear leadership to colleagues in a visible and highly professional manner, acting as a positive role model.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Skills &amp; Experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered General Nurse with valid NMC pin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in an Outpatients setting with surgical experience, ideally Gynaecology, ENT/Dermatology or Colorectal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in wound management, and competent in removal of all types of sutures, clips and aseptic dressings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills with the ability to prioritise and co-ordinate own workload.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Friendly and adaptable approach who is able to work as part of a team and has an awareness of clinical audit and clinical governance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are an organisation that has charitable status and this helps us to drive forward our mission of reinvesting our income to deliver better patient outcomes.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The London Clinic is proud of its diverse workforce and is committed to building a team that represents a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, and skills. We absolutely welcome applicants from underrepresented groups; if you think you have the skills and experience for the job, please apply - we would love to hear from you regardless of your background.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
